  "body": "https://enzyme.expasy.org/EC/1.13.11.37\r\nEntry: EC:1.13.11.37\r\nAccepted Name: hydroxyquinol 1,2-dioxygenase\r\nReaction catalysed: benzene-1,2,4-triol + O2 <=> 2 H(+) + maleylacetate\r\n\r\nThat EC is currently on two GO terms (shown below), it's an exact match for the second one (GO:0047074) that describes the 'complete 2-step reaction', but should only be a 'broadMatch' for the first one (GO:0018581) that only describes the first step of the reaction. (The second step in non-enzymatic conversion of 3-hydroxy-cis,cis-muconate to maleylacetate - see https://biocyc.org/META/NEW-IMAGE?type=REACTION&object=RXN-10137)\r\nTasks:\r\n- [x] Make EC:1.13.11.37 xref on GO:0018581 a 'broadMatch'\r\n- [x] Remove EC:1.13.11.37-attributed synonyms from GO:0018581 (EC:1.13.11.37 currently doesn't list any synonyms)\r\n- [x] Change GO:0018581 def attribution to use RHEA:19441\r\n- [x] Make EC:1.13.11.37 xref on GO:0047074 a 'exactMatch'\r\n- [x] Tweak GO:0047074 def to match EC:1.13.11.37 def\r\n\r\n\r\nid: GO:0018581\r\nname: hydroxyquinol 1,2-dioxygenase activity\r\ndef: \"Catalysis of the reaction: benzene-1,2,4-triol + O2 = 3-hydroxy-cis,cis-muconate.\" [EC:1.13.11.37]\r\nsynonym: \"benzene-1,2,4-triol:oxygen 1,2-oxidoreductase (decyclizing)\" RELATED [EC:1.13.11.37]\r\nsynonym: \"hydroxyquinol dioxygenase activity\" RELATED [EC:1.13.11.37]\r\nxref: EC:1.13.11.37\r\nxref: MetaCyc:HYDROXYQUINOL-12-DIOXYGENASE-RXN\r\nxref: RHEA:19441\r\nxref: UM-BBD_reactionID:r0232\r\nis_a: GO:0016702 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on single donors with incorporation of molecular oxygen, incorporation of two atoms of oxygen\r\n\r\nid: GO:0047074\r\nname: 4-hydroxycatechol 1,2-dioxygenase activity\r\nnamespace: molecular_function\r\ndef: \"Catalysis of the reaction: O2 + benzene-1,2,4-triol = maleylacetate.\" [RHEA:35595]\r\nxref: EC:1.13.11.37\r\nxref: MetaCyc:R308-RXN\r\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-10137\r\nxref: RHEA:35595\r\nis_a: GO:0016702 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on single donors with incorporation of molecular oxygen, incorporation of two atoms of oxygen\r\n\r\n\r\n",
